## Launching a private server

My private server has its own dedicated security group because that security group controls the affairs of how apps talk to themselves, within that server

My private server's security group's source is Public Security Group, which means that only resources available in the public subnet can access or communicate with resources in the Private subnet, rather than keeping it open and accessible to anyone over the internet with 0.0.0.0/0

